\* GENERATED by the TLC-SL compiler from II-001 — Mastery before advance.
\* Article Instructional Integrity / Mastery Learning. Enforcement BLOCK.
\* STATUS: emitted, NOT yet checked by TLC in this build. See tla.mjs header.
EXTENDS TLC

VARIABLES mastery, unit
vars == << mastery, unit >>

TypeOK ==
  /\ mastery \in { "not_demonstrated", "demonstrated" }
  /\ unit \in { "current", "advanced" }

Init ==
  /\ mastery = "not_demonstrated"
  /\ unit = "current"

Op_DEMONSTRATE_MASTERY ==
  /\ TRUE
  /\ mastery' = "demonstrated"
  /\ UNCHANGED << unit >>

Op_ADVANCE ==
  /\ (mastery = "demonstrated")
  /\ unit' = "advanced"
  /\ UNCHANGED << mastery >>

Next ==
  \/ Op_DEMONSTRATE_MASTERY
  \/ Op_ADVANCE

Spec == Init /\ [][Next]_vars

\* Safety property (Constitution Instructional Integrity / Mastery Learning):
Safety == ((unit = "advanced") => (mastery = "demonstrated"))
